So.. not sure if this discussion has already taken place.<br>
I came here to hear your opinion on something.<br>
<br>
<br>
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<br>
Silvery Belt of Contention <br>
LORE ITEM MAGIC ITEM <br>
AC: +10 Sta: +4 Wis: +5 Int: +5 <br>
Weight: 0.0 <br>
Classes: All Classes <br>
Races: All Races <br>
Inventory Slot: Waist<br>
Velious Required: Yes <br>
Can be stored in Medium and larger containers <br>
<br>
Effect: Haste <br>
Type: Permanent <br>
Charges: Unlimited <br>
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~ <br>
<br>
<br>
Okay. One of these drops in Kael last night. Although it's ALL/ALL, the raid leader asks Melee's to roll. (This was a guild raid with guests invited.. I am a paladin)<br>
<br>
I won with a 100 and was ecstatic!<br>
<br>
My FBSS quickly went to a warrior in the guild who still had no haste belt at 55. <br>
<br>
Then, ANOTHER one drops!!!<br>
<br>
57 Monk wins the roll, he quickly passes his FBSS down to a Ranger that had no haste belt.<br>
<br>
<br>
All is right in the world, the winners are giddy and the melees that get new FBSS's are thrilled too. Our tanks/melee are getting stronger!<br>
<br>
*Sigh*<br>
Or so we thought.<br>
<br>
<br>
Later on, i find out some casters were peeved about not being able to roll on this item.<br>
<br>
I mean *REALLY* peeved. I was shocked. <br>
<br>
<br>
Then, my enchanter friend sends me a tell <br>
&quot;Hey, i see you're in Kael tonight! Win any goodies!?  &quot; <br>
<br>
&quot;YES! I won a Silvery Belt of Contention!!! This thing is a Hybrid dream come true!!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Oh man!!! I want one of those SO badly! The Melee in my group never let me roll!&quot;<br>
<br>
<br>
Um... i just couldn't believe any casters would even dream of rolling against melee for this item. <br>
<br>
Now, you may be thinking.. sure, you're a paladin. Of course you don't understand why. But, i play an Enchanter too... and would *never* roll against a melee for this belt.<br>
<br>
<br>
So, i guess after all this, i'm asking... what's the rule of thumb your guild or group uses when this item drops? <br>
<br>
All roll?<br>
Melee only roll?<br>
<br>
<br>
Would love to hear what you have to say on the matter.<br>
<br>
